'''Richard Garrigues''' is a naturalist, writer and videographer, originally from suburban New Jersey, who has lived in [[Costa Rica]] since 1981, where he leads [[birding]] and [[natural history]] tours. Since April 2000, he has been posting the [http://www.angelfire.com/bc/gonebirding/ ''Gone Birding Newsletter''] on line. In June 2005 he began also to study the birds of northwestern [[Ecuador]]. <ref>[http://ibc.hbw.com/ibc/phtml/contributor.phtml?idContributor=79 ''Handbook of the Birds of the World.'']</ref>
==Published works== *''The Birds of Costa Rica'', illustrated by Robert Dean, 2007 ({{ISBN|080147373X}}) *''The birds of Costa Rica, a field guide'', Second edition illustrated by Robert Dean, 2014
